title: Writing Seminars: Who is an African American
yc_attrs: This course can be applied towards the Writing Yale College distributional requirement.
description: Instruction in writing well-reasoned analyses and academic arguments, with emphasis on the importance of reading, research, and revision. Using examples of nonfiction prose from a variety of academic disciplines, individual sections focus on topics such as the city, childhood, globalization, inequality, food culture, sports, and war.Â Preregistration required; see under English Department.
regnotes: Enrollment for this course is managed through Preference Selection
